<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Canterbury-west-Winter-Highsmith.jpeg" title="Enlarge"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6b/Magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" /></a></div>
<a href="Ezra_Winter" title="Ezra Winter">Ezra Winter</a>, Canterbury tales mural (1939), <a href="Library_of_Congress" title="Library of Congress">Library of Congress</a> <a href="John_Adams_Building" title="John Adams Building">John Adams Building</a>, Washington, D.C. This mural is located on the west wall of the North Reading Room, and features the Miller, Host, Knight, Squire, Yeoman, Doctor, Chaucer, Man of Law, Clerk, Manciple, Sailor, Prioress, Nun and three Priests; the other pilgrims appear on the east wall mural.<sup id="cite_ref-61" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-61"><span>[</span>61<span>]</span></a></sup></div>
